  "summary": "Malicious code in req-parmas-valid (npm)",
  "details": "Req-parmas-valid@1.0.2 is a typosquat of the 'request' HTTP library (a misspelling of 'params' with 'valid' appended). On require(), index.js spawns a detached node child process running lib/callers.js, which makes an HTTPS GET to jsonkeeper[.]com/b/DDC6J with a custom X-Secret-Key header and executes the response via the Function constructor with full require access, delivering a second-stage payload. The package is a single-version burst from an unknown domain and impersonates the real request project's GitHub bugs URL.",
